</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">the same restrictions and Penalties as retiring Partners of the said Old Company are liable to under their aforesaid Articles of agreement of the fifth day of July one thousand eight hundred and two<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Art. 6</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">That although the said New Company are by the present agreement limited to one fourth Part of the said Joint Trade to be carried on from Canada into the Interior Country yet should Circumstances arise in the Course of events that should enable the said Joint Company to obtain a Participation in the General Trade and Rights of the Hudson Bay Company or the whole thereof by purchase then and in that case it is hereby covenant and agreed that the numbers who shall their represent the said new Company shall not be hereby precluded from nigociating with the their representatives of the said Old Company for a more extensive Participation in the said Joint Concern which thereby shall or may be formed or extended and for such Quantum hereof as shall be agreed upon; But it is understood that any permission which may be obtained from the said Hudson Bay Company for a partial transit of Merchandise or returns through their Territories shall not be considered as forming a Ground for the Nigociation of such increased Participation; and it is also understood that the said new Company shall Sustain no part of the Expences which have</p>
